<p><a href="https://github.com/sponsors/patriciogonzalezvivo"><img alt="" src="https://img.shields.io/static/v1?label=Sponsor&amp;message=%E2%9D%A4&amp;logo=GitHub"></a></p>
<h2>psrdnoise  (<a href="/"><code>lygia</code></a>/<a href="/generative"><code>generative</code></a>/<a href="/generative/psrdnoise"><code>psrdnoise</code></a>)</h2>
<p>Tiling simplex flow noise in 2-D and 3-D from <a href="\<a href="https://github.com/stegu/psrdnoise">https://github.com/stegu/psrdnoise\</a>"><a href="https://github.com/stegu/psrdnoise">https://github.com/stegu/psrdnoise</a></a>
"vec2/3 x" is the point to evaluate,
"vec2/3 period" is the desired periods 
"float alpha" is the rotation (in radians) for the swirling gradients.
The "float" return value is the noise value n,
the "out gradient" argument returns the first order derivatives,
and "out dg" returns the second order derivatives as (dn2/dx2, dn2/dy2, dn2/dxy)
For the original code please visit: <a href="\<a href="https://github.com/stegu/psrdnoise">https://github.com/stegu/psrdnoise\</a>"><a href="https://github.com/stegu/psrdnoise">https://github.com/stegu/psrdnoise</a></a></p>
